caption: Table 2:  Accuracy for the dog recognition task.
references: Table 2 shows the results, where we apply the Wav2Vec2 model to dog identification. Our results are in line with the results from Pérez-Espinosa et al. (2018); Molnár et al. (2009), and demonstrate that effectiveness of acoustic representations to discriminate between individual dogs. Further, we find that a model pre-trained on human speech significantly outperforms the model trained from scratch.
